The Enterprise and Innovation Programme is intended to serve entrepreneurs and businesses to raise funds for innovative entrepreneurship.
Companies should raise funding to introduce new technologies, for industrial research, but also for the implementation of more effective organisational methods.
In the current absorption of money from EU funds, the Czech Republic is still among the least successful in the newly admitted countries.
