What insurance is appropriate for me?
Insurance for a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a substantial expense that depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, driving licence time, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to figure out what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract stipulating that the insurance company receives an agreed insured amount of a certain amount for taking responsibility for paying the damages in the event of an insured event.
The insurance is the cost of the insurance, which is determined with regard to various factors such as age, condition, gender, duration of possession of the driving licence, the type of vehicle insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the more likely there is a crash, the higher the premium rate.
For this reason, both those over 25 years of age or women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, the insurance companies concluded that those living in the marriage tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journeys and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
The growth in the frequency of the journeys increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the cost of premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well to choose the kind of insurance that best matches his profile of the insured person.
We will show ourselves the most important variables for the selection of this type of insurance or another, which, in addition to the fact that it meets the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 experience various drawbacks, such as little driving experience and short possession of a driving licence when they want to take out premiums at an affordable price.
Although the ideal for good coverage is insurance against all risks, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks at a premium discount to obtain the insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would presuppose a client's co-financing in the event of a claim.
"Part of the payment of the insurance claim provided by the client will be set in advance when determining the price of the premium, which will be the higher, which would be the lower, the co-payment," explains Luis Noguera, the senior head of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other traffic participants by insuring the client against the damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as possible, as this will affect your bonus and make it possible to reduce premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
By contrast, malus is an increase in that basic rate.
"The Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the twenty-five-year mark, it is easier for drivers to take out insurance, as the client's risk index is reduced, thanks to their experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people are usually unable to take advantage of the experience gained in advance when the accident is made, nor in the process of driving," assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of proceedings, when the 'fear of the newcomer's has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be a clientele with the lowest risk index and thus their surprings will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks at the discount of the premium (which could be €300) or, in the case of a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their proceedings are calmer and their purchaseability is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to insure against all risks at a discounted premium (which is €150) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation if a high bonus has been achieved.
It has to be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a valid reason to study the possibilities of insurance that would suit us best in view of our personal situation.
